thor/Ke Ma","target":"Author/Ke Ma","line":95},{"title":"Author/Ke Ma","target":"Author/Ke Ma","line":96},{"title":"Author/Yan Pei","target":"Author/Yan Pei","line":97},{"title":"Author/Yunfei Pei","target":"Author/Yunfei Pei","line":98},{"title":"Author/Hongwei Liu","target":"Author/Hongwei Liu","line":99},{"title":"Author/Hongwei Liu","target":"Author/Hongwei Liu","line":100},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/wang_erinacerins_2015/wang_erinacerins_2015.pdf","line":102}],"metadata":{"id":"wang_erinacerins_2015","type":"article-journal","title":"Erinacerins C-L, isoindolin-1-ones with α-glucosidase inhibitory activity from cultures of the medicinal mushroom Hericium erinaceus.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2015]]},"DOI":"10.1021/np5004388","container-title":"Journal of Natural Products","abstract":"The well-known edible and medicinal mushroom Hericium erinaceus produces various bioactive secondary metabolites. Ten new isoindolin-1-ones, named erinacerins C–L (1–10), together with (E)-5-(3,7-dimethylocta-2,6-dien-1-yl)-4-hydroxy-6-methoxy-2-phenethylisoindolin-1-one (11) were isolated from the solid culture of H. erinaceus. The structures of new metabolites were established by spectroscopic methods. The absolute configurations of 3, 4, 9, and 10 were assigned by comparing their specific rotations with those of related phthalimidines (13–20). Compounds 5 and 6, 7 and 8, and 9 and 10 are double-bond positional isomers. In a α-glucosidase inhibition assay, compounds 2–11 showed inhibitory activity with IC50 values ranging from 5.3 to 145.1 μM. Preliminary structure–activity analysis indicated that the terpenoid side chain and the phenolic hydroxy groups contributed greatly to the α-glucosidase inhibitory activity of 1–11. In a cytotoxicity assay, compound 11 also presented weak cytotoxicity against two ...","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Wang","given":"Kai","literal":""},{"family":"Li","given":"Bao","literal":""},{"family":"Bao","given":"Li","literal":""},{"family":"Qi","given":"Qiu-Yue","literal":""},{"family":"Qi","given":"Qiu-Yue","literal":""},{"family":"Zhao","given":"Feng","literal":""},{"family":"Zhao","given":"Feng","literal":""},{"family":"Ma","given":"Ke","literal":""},{"family":"Ma","given":"Ke","literal":""},{"family":"Pei","given":"Yan","literal":""},{"family":"Pei","given":"Yunfei","literal":""},{"family":"Liu","given":"Hongwei","literal":""},{"family":"Liu","given":"Hongwei","literal":""}],"citation-key":"wang_erinacerins_2015","year":"2015","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Erinacerins C-L, isoindolin-1-ones with α-glucosidase inhibitory activity from cultures of the medicinal mushroom Hericium erinaceus."],"author-links":["[[Author/Kai Wang]]","[[Author/Kai Wang]]","[[Author/Kai Wang]]","[[Author/Kai Wang]]","[[Author/Kai Wang]]","[[Author/Kai Wang]]","[[Author/Kai Wang]]","[[Author/Kai Wang]]","[[Author/Bao Li]]","[[Author/Li Bao]]","[[Author/Qiu-Yue Qi]]","[[Author/Qiu-Yue Qi]]","[[Author/Feng Zhao]]","[[Author/Feng Zhao]]","[[Author/Ke Ma]]","[[Author/Ke Ma]]","[[Author/Yan Pei]]","[[Author/Yunfei Pei]]","[[Author/Hongwei Liu]]","[[Author/Hongwei Liu]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/wang_erinacerins_2015/wang_erinacerins_2015.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"om6mvc","at":1774951892118}},"smart_blocks:Research/@wang_erinacerins_2015.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[-0.04116177,-0.04790108,-0.02314579,-0.05329942,0.02758167,0.0184479,0.03444757,0.0229755,-0.06486276,0.0098439,0.04181938,-0.01610654,0.04149014,0.02031669,0.03819052,0.01033791,0.02864333,